WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:50.470 --> 00:01:54.290
<b>The Town of Celebration</b>

21
00:01:56.330 --> 00:01:58.040
Alright! Done!

22
00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:01.990
This is the man that fell
from the sky, Mr. Snow Barrel!

23
00:02:03.230 --> 00:02:06.230
That's such a crude snowman...

24
00:02:06.230 --> 00:02:06.810
What?!

25
00:02:07.900 --> 00:02:12.020
Look at my soulful artwork,
the Snow Queen!

26
00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:13.910
Whoa! That's incredible!

27
00:02:13.910 --> 00:02:15.880
Okay then! Snow Barrel Punch!

28
00:02:21.510 --> 00:02:24.250
What the hell are you doing?!

29
00:02:24.250 --> 00:02:25.580
Ahh! Mr. Snow Barrel!

30
00:02:25.580 --> 00:02:26.820
How dare you...!

31
00:02:26.820 --> 00:02:30.620
How come they're so energetic
when it's this cold?

32
00:02:26.820 --> 00:02:28.920
Damn you! Damn you!
Damn you! Damn you!

33
00:02:35.170 --> 00:02:38.040
Nami! How much snow shoveling
of love would you like me to do?!

34
00:02:38.170 --> 00:02:40.500
Please continue until
it stops snowing, Sanji!

35
00:02:40.500 --> 00:02:42.350
Yay! Nami!

36
00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:46.840
Hey, you. Doesn't this
ship have a heater?

37
00:02:46.840 --> 00:02:48.180
I'm cold.

38
00:02:48.180 --> 00:02:52.620
Shut up! You guys aren't guests!
Go help shovel snow or something!

39
00:02:55.520 --> 00:02:57.190
Lightning?!

40
00:02:57.190 --> 00:02:59.900
What the heck is up with
the weather around here?!

41
00:03:03.860 --> 00:03:06.030
It was sunny up until recently.

42
00:03:06.030 --> 00:03:09.200
The next moment, it started
snowing, and now lightning...

43
00:03:09.200 --> 00:03:12.200
The seasons, as well as
the weather, go around randomly.

44
00:03:12.200 --> 00:03:14.050
It's just like what Crocus said.

45
00:03:14.050 --> 00:03:17.390
It seems that you guys are
clueless about the Grand Line.

46
00:03:17.390 --> 00:03:21.990
You haven't been steering for
a while now. Is that really okay?

47
00:03:21.990 --> 00:03:24.220
I just checked the direction.

48
00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:27.120
Ahhhh!

49
00:03:27.160 --> 00:03:28.670
Wh... What?

50
00:03:28.670 --> 00:03:30.000
What's the matter?

51
00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:31.960
What's wrong, Nami?!

52
00:03:32.340 --> 00:03:34.230
Ahhh... No way!

53
00:03:34.340 --> 00:03:37.340
Turn the ship around
180 degrees! Hurry!

54
00:03:37.340 --> 00:03:40.040
Turn it 180 degrees?! Why, are we going back?

55
00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:41.470
Did you forget something?

56
00:03:41.710 --> 00:03:44.980
The ship has turned around and is
going in the opposite direction!

57
00:03:44.980 --> 00:03:47.790
When I looked away from the
log pose for a second...

58
00:03:48.480 --> 00:03:50.150
The waves were calm earlier...

59
00:03:50.350 --> 00:03:53.220
Are you really a navigator?

60
00:03:53.650 --> 00:03:59.890
In this sea, you can't trust the winds,
sky, waves, clouds... anything...

61
00:03:59.890 --> 00:04:04.030
The only thing that doesn't change is
the direction that the log pose points.

62
00:04:04.030 --> 00:04:05.730
Do you understand that?

63
00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:11.040
Stop bossing me around in those
cozy blankets and go help already!

64
00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:12.380
Brace the yard!

65
00:04:12.380 --> 00:04:15.570
Receive the wind from the starboard!
Turn the ship 180 degrees to the left!

66
00:04:15.910 --> 00:04:17.370
Usopp! Take care of the lateen sail!

67
00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:17.370
Got it!

68
00:04:17.370 --> 00:04:19.410
Sanji! Take the helm!

69
00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:19.410
Leave it to me, Nami!

70
00:04:19.650 --> 00:04:20.980
You guys! I'm counting on you!

71
00:04:20.980 --> 00:04:23.650
She's such a slave driver.

72
00:04:23.650 --> 00:04:25.990
Hey, wait! The wind has changed.

73
00:04:25.990 --> 00:04:27.360
No way!

74
00:04:30.990 --> 00:04:32.330
It's the first spring gale!

75
00:04:32.330 --> 00:04:33.330
Why?!

76
00:04:33.330 --> 00:04:36.160
Don't just sleep there while
the snow accumulates on you!

77
00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:41.840
Hey! I saw a dolphin jump
over there! Let's go there.

78
00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:43.470
You keep quiet!

79
00:04:43.840 --> 00:04:45.410
The waves are getting high!

80
00:04:45.410 --> 00:04:47.440
I see an iceberg in
the ten o'clock direction!

81
00:04:47.700 --> 00:04:49.280
Nami! It's getting foggy!

82
00:04:49.280 --> 00:04:51.850
What the hell's with this sea?!

83
00:04:51.850 --> 00:04:55.040
W-W... We're gonna crash!

84
00:04:57.660 --> 00:04:59.660
Hey! Water's leaking at
the bottom of the ship!

85
00:04:59.660 --> 00:05:00.830
We have to patch it right away!

86
00:05:00.830 --> 00:05:01.710
Got it!

87
00:05:05.630 --> 00:05:07.220
The clouds are moving fast!

88
00:05:07.300 --> 00:05:09.540
Unfurl the sails!
That wind is too strong!

89
00:05:09.540 --> 00:05:12.140
If we take it directly, we'll overturn!

90
00:05:12.140 --> 00:05:14.800
Everyone! Eat this!
Let's gather our strength!

91
00:05:17.640 --> 00:05:19.470
You're eating too much!

92
00:05:22.480 --> 00:05:24.480
Oh crap! The sail is gonna be torn!

93
00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:26.720
Forget about things up here.
Go fix the bottom of the ship!

94
00:05:26.720 --> 00:05:28.490
There's another part of the
bottom of the ship damaged!

95
00:05:28.490 --> 00:05:29.650
Dammit!

96
00:05:55.780 --> 00:05:57.880
Ahhh, that felt good.

97
00:06:07.280 --> 00:06:11.890
Hey, no matter how nice the weather is,
you guys shouldn't be so lazy.

98
00:06:12.470 --> 00:06:14.890
We'd better be on the right track.

99
00:06:14.890 --> 00:06:17.530
– You...
– You...

100
00:06:17.530 --> 00:06:18.800
Hm?

101
00:06:18.800 --> 00:06:20.810
Why're you guys on this ship?

102
00:06:20.810 --> 00:06:22.540
You're slow!

103
00:06:22.540 --> 00:06:26.810
We're heading to their town
right now. It's called Whisky Peak.

104
00:06:26.810 --> 00:06:30.480
You mean we're taking them back?
We don't owe them anything.

105
00:06:30.480 --> 00:06:32.820
Right, we don't.

106
00:06:32.820 --> 00:06:35.490
Well, not like it matters to me...

107
00:06:35.490 --> 00:06:38.820
Yeah, your faces say that
you're thinking bad thoughts.

108
00:06:38.820 --> 00:06:41.490
What were your names again?

109
00:06:41.890 --> 00:06:44.420
I-I'm Mr. 9.

110
00:06:44.960 --> 00:06:46.760
I'm Miss Wednesday.

111
00:06:47.260 --> 00:06:48.260
Right...

112
00:06:48.260 --> 00:06:52.330
Something has been bothering me
ever since I first heard your names...

113
00:06:52.770 --> 00:06:57.440
I feel like I've heard them
somewhere before, or maybe not...

114
00:06:57.440 --> 00:06:59.780
Well, either way...

115
00:07:02.110 --> 00:07:06.120
How dare you sleep
comfortably all this time...

116
00:07:06.120 --> 00:07:09.460
You kept sleeping no matter how
many times we tried to wake you up...

117
00:07:09.460 --> 00:07:10.620
What?!

118
00:07:15.790 --> 00:07:17.290
Don't let your guard down, everyone!

119
00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:19.920
We don't know
what else might happen.

120
00:07:20.260 --> 00:07:22.760
I was finally able to realize
the danger of this sea just now.

121
00:07:23.090 --> 00:07:25.700
I was able to understand the reason
why it's called the Grand Line.

122
00:07:26.830 --> 00:07:31.940
There's no doubt about it since
my navigation skills don't work at all.

123
00:07:32.480 --> 00:07:36.820
How blunt... Are we gonna be okay?

124
00:07:36.820 --> 00:07:40.490
We'll be fine! Things will
still work out for sure.

125
00:07:40.490 --> 00:07:42.150
In fact...

126
00:07:42.150 --> 00:07:43.150
Look!

127
00:07:43.550 --> 00:07:45.670
Our first journey is over.

128
00:07:58.280 --> 00:07:59.700
It's an island!

129
00:08:01.770 --> 00:08:04.780
So this is Whiskey Peak...

130
00:08:04.780 --> 00:08:07.450
But it's really a funny-looking island.

131
00:08:07.450 --> 00:08:09.920
Those cacti are huge!

132
00:08:13.240 --> 00:08:14.240
Huh?

133
00:08:14.240 --> 00:08:15.910
Well then, we'll be leaving now.

134
00:08:15.910 --> 00:08:18.240
Thanks for taking us home, honeys.

135
00:08:18.240 --> 00:08:20.220
If we're linked by fate,
we'll meet again!

136
00:08:21.080 --> 00:08:22.910
– Bye bye, baby!
– Bye bye, baby!

137
00:08:25.110 --> 00:08:25.990
Huh?

138
00:08:25.990 --> 00:08:27.490
They're gone...

139
00:08:27.490 --> 00:08:29.730
Who could they have been?

140
00:08:29.730 --> 00:08:31.820
Who cares?! We're landing!

141
00:08:32.830 --> 00:08:37.160
There's a river at the front.
Looks like we can go inland by ship.

142
00:08:39.170 --> 00:08:43.170
I-Isn't it possible that there're
monsters or things like that?

143
00:08:43.170 --> 00:08:46.940
It's definitely possible.
This is the Grand Line.

144
00:08:46.940 --> 00:08:50.510
If we come across monsters,
we can just leave the island.

145
00:08:50.510 --> 00:08:51.710
Hold on a sec.

146
00:08:51.710 --> 00:08:57.520
Don't forget that we have to stay on
this island for a certain period of time.

147
00:08:57.520 --> 00:08:58.590
Why?

148
00:08:59.090 --> 00:09:02.390
Unless we store the magnetism
of this island in the log pose,

149
00:09:02.390 --> 00:09:04.860
we can't go to the next island.

150
00:09:04.860 --> 00:09:07.860
Since each island requires a different
amount of time to store the log,

151
00:09:07.860 --> 00:09:11.370
some islands require only several
hours while others require days.

152
00:09:11.370 --> 00:09:15.370
Th-Then even if this is a monster island
that we want to escape from right away,

153
00:09:15.370 --> 00:09:19.210
it's possible that we have to stay
here for days until the log is stored?

154
00:09:19.210 --> 00:09:21.540
That's right.

155
00:09:21.540 --> 00:09:25.210
Well, we can think about that
when it happens. Let's go already!

156
00:09:25.210 --> 00:09:29.220
Luffy's right. Let's go.
It's not worth thinking about it.

157
00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:33.560
No matter what happens,
I'll protect Nami.

158
00:09:33.560 --> 00:09:37.560
H-hey, wait. Listen, everyone.
My chronic illness is suddenly...

159
00:09:37.560 --> 00:09:39.330
My "can't-get-on-
this-island" disease is–

160
00:09:39.330 --> 00:09:40.820
Then we're going in.

161
00:09:40.820 --> 00:09:41.570
Listen.

162
00:09:41.570 --> 00:09:43.900
Make sure you're prepared
to run as well as fight.

163
00:09:41.580 --> 00:09:42.420
No...

164
00:09:43.900 --> 00:09:48.840
Ah, well... like I said,
my chronic illness is...

165
00:09:48.840 --> 00:09:50.510
Well, I guess you're not listening...

166
00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:52.970
I wonder what'll appear...

167
00:09:59.330 --> 00:10:01.990
Hey, it's a pirate ship.

168
00:10:03.670 --> 00:10:05.660
Pirates are here!

169
00:10:11.230 --> 00:10:13.890
Huh? Something's moving.

170
00:10:13.890 --> 00:10:16.130
Humans? Humans are there!

171
00:10:25.870 --> 00:10:27.850
Welcome to the Grand Line!

172
00:10:27.850 --> 00:10:29.520
Welcome to our town!

173
00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:32.020
To the welcoming town, Whisky Peak!

174
00:10:32.530 --> 00:10:36.390
F... Far from monsters,
we're being welcomed!

175
00:10:39.200 --> 00:10:40.760
What's going on?

176
00:10:40.760 --> 00:10:43.200
Pirates! Welcome to our town!

177
00:10:43.200 --> 00:10:46.440
Hooray for the heroes on the sea!

178
00:10:50.210 --> 00:10:53.210
Whoa! There're lots of cute girls!

179
00:10:53.210 --> 00:10:56.210
Ahh! Look this way! They're handsome!

180
00:10:57.880 --> 00:11:02.610
Maybe pirates are
people's heroes after all.

181
00:11:02.610 --> 00:11:04.780
Heeeey!

182
00:11:08.830 --> 00:11:10.160
Welco...

183
00:11:12.500 --> 00:11:14.170
♪ Ma-ma-ma... ♪

184
00:11:14.170 --> 00:11:15.790
Welcome.

185
00:11:15.810 --> 00:11:23.960
<b>Igarappoi
Mayor of Whisky Peak</b>

186
00:11:18.820 --> 00:11:20.900
My name is Igarappoi.

187
00:11:20.900 --> 00:11:23.960
I'm the mayor of Whisky Peak.

188
00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:26.830
Okay. I'm Luffy. Nice to meet you.

189
00:11:26.830 --> 00:11:28.800
Pops, you went overboard
on curling your hair.

190
00:11:28.800 --> 00:11:32.830
Whisky Peak is a town that thrives
on making liquor and music.

191
00:11:32.830 --> 00:11:35.310
Hospitality is the pride of our town.

192
00:11:35.310 --> 00:11:37.840
As for our proud liquor,
it's as bountiful as the seawater.

193
00:11:37.840 --> 00:11:40.820
Would you allow us to
throw a party for you

194
00:11:40.820 --> 00:11:43.280
so that we may hear your tales of...

195
00:11:44.850 --> 00:11:48.350
♪ Ma-ma-ma... ♪

196
00:11:48.350 --> 00:11:50.060
...your tales of adventure?

197
00:11:50.290 --> 00:11:51.880
– We'll be glad to!
– We'll be glad to!

198
00:11:53.190 --> 00:11:54.330
– Alright!
– Alright!

199
00:11:54.330 --> 00:11:55.770
– Yipee!
– Yahoo!

200
00:11:54.760 --> 00:11:55.770
Three idiots...

201
00:11:56.300 --> 00:11:57.800
Say, by the way,

202
00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:00.260
how long will it take for the log
of this island to be stored?

203
00:12:00.260 --> 00:12:04.000
Log? Forget such boring stuff.

204
00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:06.080
Please just rest after
such a long journey.

205
00:12:06.510 --> 00:12:11.280
Now, everyone! Prepare for the party!
Sing to entertain the adventurers!

206
00:12:11.650 --> 00:12:14.310
– Party time!
– Party time!

207
00:12:27.570 --> 00:12:30.230
Then I said with utter coolness,

208
00:12:30.230 --> 00:12:33.740
"Sea kings, don't you
touch my friends."

209
00:12:34.240 --> 00:12:37.370
– Wow...
– Captain Usopp!
– You're so amazing!

210
00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:42.580
Well, regarding the Calm Belt,
even I trembled a bit, though.

211
00:12:42.580 --> 00:12:43.590
A tremble of excitement, that is.

212
00:12:43.590 --> 00:12:44.750
– Whoa!
– Amazing!

213
00:12:44.750 --> 00:12:46.590
Cheers to Usopp!

214
00:12:47.240 --> 00:12:50.240
Whoa! Amazing!
He finished his tenth cup!

215
00:12:50.240 --> 00:12:51.420
This is it...

216
00:12:51.420 --> 00:12:54.250
I can't drink anymore.

217
00:12:54.250 --> 00:12:56.910
This girl's downing her twelfth cup!

218
00:12:58.580 --> 00:13:00.160
Take that!

219
00:13:00.160 --> 00:13:01.590
More food!

220
00:13:01.590 --> 00:13:04.920
Whoa! The captain finished
a meal for twenty people!

221
00:13:04.920 --> 00:13:07.260
The cook is down!

222
00:13:07.260 --> 00:13:09.090
Please, I can't go on...

223
00:13:09.090 --> 00:13:13.930
Whoa! This young man is trying to
hit on twenty girls at the same time!

224
00:13:13.930 --> 00:13:16.270
What's with this gang?!

225
00:13:17.270 --> 00:13:19.100
It's really a fu...

226
00:13:20.610 --> 00:13:23.280
♪ Ma-ma-ma... ♪

227
00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:24.640
a fun night!

228
00:13:24.640 --> 00:13:28.380
I'm glad that you all
seem to be having fun.

229
00:13:33.290 --> 00:13:36.660
Yes, indeed, I'm very glad...

230
00:13:37.620 --> 00:13:44.300
For that reason, we failed our
mission of securing food... however,

231
00:13:44.300 --> 00:13:52.580
we'd like to report that we succeeded
in leading the gang to Cactus Island.

232
00:13:52.580 --> 00:13:54.240
B-A-B-Y.

233
00:13:54.240 --> 00:13:59.140
All right! If we submit this, we somehow
should be able to clear our names.

234
00:13:59.140 --> 00:14:01.750
Right. I'll drop it in
the Unluckies Box immediately.

235
00:14:07.250 --> 00:14:09.410
They'll deliver it for us...

236
00:14:13.590 --> 00:14:14.920
to the boss...

237
00:14:15.930 --> 00:14:18.600
This is it. I quit. I'm gonna sleep.

238
00:14:18.600 --> 00:14:22.600
Whoa! The young man is finally
down after his thirteenth cup.

239
00:14:22.600 --> 00:14:25.940
What?! You're hopeless, Zoro!

240
00:14:25.940 --> 00:14:27.270
There're only two left.

241
00:14:27.270 --> 00:14:30.610
They're at the fifteenth cup.
She's competing against Sister.

242
00:14:30.610 --> 00:14:33.280
You should quit soon, too,
for your own sake.

243
00:14:33.280 --> 00:14:38.680
Don't be silly! I definitely won't
quit until I get the prize money.

244
00:14:40.620 --> 00:14:44.290
Ahhh! Thanks for the food.
I can't eat any more.

245
00:14:44.290 --> 00:14:46.630
Three cooks are also down!

246
00:14:46.630 --> 00:14:48.270
Glad you enjoyed it.

247
00:14:50.560 --> 00:14:52.230
I can't drink any more.

248
00:14:52.230 --> 00:14:53.630
I won!

249
00:14:56.570 --> 00:14:58.570
Ahh, what fun!

250
00:14:58.570 --> 00:15:00.280
She's finally down.

251
00:15:02.240 --> 00:15:05.580
What a nice town...

252
00:15:05.580 --> 00:15:08.070
This is a paradise.

253
00:15:17.590 --> 00:15:20.580
So they wore themselves out
partying and fell asleep...

254
00:15:23.600 --> 00:15:25.470
Sweet dreams...

255
00:15:26.930 --> 00:15:28.640
adventurers...

256
00:15:30.600 --> 00:15:33.510
Again tonight the
Cactus Rocks look beautiful,

257
00:15:33.510 --> 00:15:35.530
dancing under the moonlight.

258
00:15:38.780 --> 00:15:42.230
You're such a poet, Mr. 8.

259
00:15:42.230 --> 00:15:44.100
Oh, it's you guys...

260
00:15:45.600 --> 00:15:47.270
What happened to them?

261
00:15:47.270 --> 00:15:48.410
They've fallen...

262
00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:53.910
<b>Igarappoi, a.k.a.
Mr. 8</b>

263
00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:53.900
...to hell.

264
00:15:56.370 --> 00:16:02.710
Goodness... Since they were so stubborn,
I had to add a little alcohol to their drinks.

265
00:16:02.710 --> 00:16:05.110
Otherwise they might still be up
and having a good time.

266
00:16:05.550 --> 00:16:10.180
But was it really necessary
to put on an elaborate act...

267
00:16:13.390 --> 00:16:16.060
for just five weak looking brats?

268
00:16:13.500 --> 00:16:21.300
<b>Sister, a.k.a.
Miss Monday</b>

269
00:16:16.060 --> 00:16:18.460
We should've beat them at the harbor.

270
00:16:18.460 --> 00:16:22.260
This town is already short of food.

271
00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:25.070
Also we didn't have our hopes up
for the whale meat anyway.

272
00:16:25.070 --> 00:16:28.740
You didn't have to say it like that!
We did try our best!

273
00:16:28.740 --> 00:16:33.400
Calm down. Look at this.
I've checked them out beforehand.

274
00:16:34.750 --> 00:16:36.750
– Th-Thirty million belly?!
– Th-Thirty million belly?!

275
00:16:36.750 --> 00:16:38.280
Them?!

276
00:16:38.520 --> 00:16:43.580
It's foolish to judge a pirate's ability
based on their looks, Miss Mon–

277
00:16:45.420 --> 00:16:47.220
♪ Ma-ma-ma... ♪

278
00:16:47.220 --> 00:16:49.430
Miss Monday.

279
00:16:49.430 --> 00:16:51.490
S-Sorry.

280
00:16:51.930 --> 00:16:54.200
But we've already settled.

281
00:16:54.200 --> 00:16:56.430
Looks like we can send
a good report to the boss.

282
00:16:56.430 --> 00:16:59.770
Confiscate all the money and other
valuables on the ship immediately.

283
00:16:59.770 --> 00:17:02.760
If we kill them, the bounty
drops by thirty percent.

284
00:17:02.760 --> 00:17:06.780
The government wants
to hold public executions.

285
00:17:07.280 --> 00:17:10.410
Hey... Sorry, but...

286
00:17:11.950 --> 00:17:14.620
do you mind letting them sleep?

287
00:17:14.620 --> 00:17:17.490
They're all exhausted from
the journey this afternoon.

288
00:17:22.960 --> 00:17:24.630
Mr. 8! Miss Monday!

289
00:17:24.630 --> 00:17:27.130
The guy with the bellyband escaped from
the room when we weren't looking!

290
00:17:27.970 --> 00:17:29.770
He's over there.

291
00:17:29.770 --> 00:17:33.780
You bastard...! I thought
you were completely asleep!

292
00:17:33.780 --> 00:17:38.910
Swordsmen never make the mistake of
letting their guard down that much.

293
00:17:38.910 --> 00:17:42.980
So, let's see if I've got this right.
This is a nest of bounty hunters.

294
00:17:44.250 --> 00:17:47.420
You dupe pirates
who are in high spirits

295
00:17:47.420 --> 00:17:49.750
after having just
entered the Grand Line.

296
00:17:50.590 --> 00:17:55.260
Looks like there're about
100 bounty hunters here.

297
00:17:55.260 --> 00:17:56.430
I'll fight you all...

298
00:17:57.330 --> 00:17:59.270
Baroque Works!

299
00:17:59.270 --> 00:18:02.600
You bastard! How is it that
you know our company's name?!

300
00:18:02.600 --> 00:18:04.890
Long ago, when I was
in your line of work,

301
00:18:04.890 --> 00:18:07.940
your organization tried to recruit me.

302
00:18:07.940 --> 00:18:10.280
Naturally, I rejected it.

303
00:18:10.280 --> 00:18:14.950
Employees don't know each other's
identity and are called by code names.

304
00:18:14.950 --> 00:18:18.620
And of course, the boss' identity and his
whereabouts are a mystery to everyone.

305
00:18:18.620 --> 00:18:23.690
You're all a bunch of crooks who
loyally obey him, Baroque Works.

306
00:18:23.960 --> 00:18:26.520
Hmph! Was it a secret?

307
00:18:27.960 --> 00:18:31.200
This is surprising...

308
00:18:31.200 --> 00:18:33.400
If you know our secrets,

309
00:18:33.400 --> 00:18:36.070
then we have no other
choice but to kill you.

310
00:18:38.040 --> 00:18:39.520
Another gravestone...

311
00:18:40.900 --> 00:18:43.390
will be added to the Cactus Rocks...

312
00:19:09.270 --> 00:19:10.760
Kill him!

313
00:19:18.300 --> 00:19:19.520
H... He's gone!

314
00:19:19.520 --> 00:19:21.630
Wh-Where the heck
did he disappear to?!

315
00:19:24.540 --> 00:19:25.820
– Ahh!
– What?!

316
00:19:32.780 --> 00:19:33.840
All right then.

317
00:19:34.560 --> 00:19:35.830
Shall we?

318
00:19:36.060 --> 00:19:38.260
How dare you mock us!

319
00:19:38.270 --> 00:19:40.060
Fire!

320
00:19:43.520 --> 00:19:46.190
Idiots! They shot each other!

321
00:19:46.190 --> 00:19:47.640
H-He disappeared again!

322
00:19:50.500 --> 00:19:53.200
Kill him already!
It's just a single swordsman!

323
00:19:58.730 --> 00:20:00.970
Let me ask you a question.

324
00:20:00.970 --> 00:20:03.420
Are you sure that you need
to add only one gravestone?

325
00:20:06.640 --> 00:20:07.990
There he is!

326
00:20:08.990 --> 00:20:11.290
I-Idiots! Don't! Are you
gonna shoot me, too?!

327
00:20:11.910 --> 00:20:12.930
Stop!

328
00:20:12.930 --> 00:20:14.630
Igarappa!

329
00:20:23.250 --> 00:20:26.920
Where did that man disappear to?

330
00:20:27.740 --> 00:20:29.580
Phew...

331
00:20:29.580 --> 00:20:33.980
So that's a shotgun?
That thing sure is dangerous.

332
00:20:33.980 --> 00:20:38.780
It seems he's good enough
that even we must be cautious.

333
00:20:46.540 --> 00:20:52.050
Does he seriously think that he
can fight all of us by himself?

334
00:20:52.050 --> 00:20:57.670
It's hard to believe that he challenged us
even after knowing we're with Baroque Works.

335
00:21:10.860 --> 00:21:16.650
The new recruits that I got in Loguetown,
Yubashiri and Kitetsu III...

336
00:21:16.650 --> 00:21:20.650
This is a good chance to
try you guys out in earnest.

337
00:21:20.650 --> 00:21:23.060
I'm going to go all out!

338
00:21:23.870 --> 00:21:25.330
There you are!

339
00:21:25.960 --> 00:21:27.110
Die!

340
00:21:28.530 --> 00:21:30.070
Tch! Dammit!

341
00:21:40.490 --> 00:21:42.280
First, I'll try Yubashiri.

342
00:21:46.830 --> 00:21:49.320
It's light! This is a good sword!

343
00:21:54.340 --> 00:21:56.270
There he is! This way!

344
00:21:56.270 --> 00:21:58.170
Hold it!

345
00:21:58.170 --> 00:22:00.170
Looks like they found me!

346
00:22:00.170 --> 00:22:01.840
He went up!

347
00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:03.840
Welcome!

348
00:22:03.840 --> 00:22:06.180
Whoa! That thing's dangerous!

349
00:22:06.180 --> 00:22:07.770
This is it for you.

350
00:22:10.520 --> 00:22:11.610
Miss Monday!

351
00:22:14.520 --> 00:22:17.690
Ahh... That was an expensive drink.

352
00:22:17.690 --> 00:22:19.390
What a waste!

353
00:22:24.530 --> 00:22:26.800
What was that feeling in my hand just now?!

354
00:22:26.800 --> 00:22:29.670
How sharp this Kitetsu III is!

355
00:22:29.670 --> 00:22:33.470
A named blade should only cut
when its master wishes it,

356
00:22:33.470 --> 00:22:35.360
but this one is a problem child.

357
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:39.770
Huh?

358
00:22:39.770 --> 00:22:42.130
Lord have mercy!

359
00:22:42.130 --> 00:22:46.100
Lord have mercy! Please save us!

360
00:22:46.100 --> 00:22:48.190
Merciful Lord Blinding Powder!

361
00:22:49.600 --> 00:22:53.760
You should use such a cheap trick
on someone with a pure heart.

362
00:22:55.770 --> 00:22:57.600
I used the back of the blade,
so forgive me.

363
00:23:00.540 --> 00:23:02.110
He went further up!

364
00:23:02.110 --> 00:23:02.860
Corner him!

365
00:23:04.450 --> 00:23:06.620
There's nowhere to escape up there!

366
00:23:10.690 --> 00:23:13.020
S-Stop it!

367
00:23:13.020 --> 00:23:14.960
Help me! Help me!

368
00:23:22.360 --> 00:23:24.360
The ladder's falling!

369
00:23:27.370 --> 00:23:30.120
Ahh! He's jumping over here!

370
00:23:31.710 --> 00:23:32.700
Shoot him!

371
00:23:33.830 --> 00:23:34.860
Two-Sword Style:

372
00:23:37.900 --> 00:23:39.370
Hawk Surge!

373
00:23:48.890 --> 00:23:51.060
Watch out. That place is unstable.

374
00:23:51.060 --> 00:23:51.820
– What?
– What?

375
00:23:56.730 --> 00:23:58.590
That was close! It grazed me!

376
00:24:04.410 --> 00:24:06.740
Don't try our patience.

377
00:24:06.740 --> 00:24:10.080
There's no man who can
best my strength.

378
00:24:13.570 --> 00:24:16.110
Superhuman...

379
00:24:17.070 --> 00:24:18.920
Brass Knuckles!

380
00:24:25.180 --> 00:24:26.680
We've wast–

381
00:24:26.680 --> 00:24:27.680
♪ Ma-ma... ♪

382
00:24:27.680 --> 00:24:31.150
We've wasted time,
but we finally settled it.

383
00:24:31.150 --> 00:24:32.090
The end!

384
00:24:33.190 --> 00:24:34.280
What?!

385
00:24:35.530 --> 00:24:38.590
M... Miss Monday!

386
00:24:40.860 --> 00:24:43.470
What's the matter, muscle woman?

387
00:24:43.870 --> 00:24:46.870
Didn't you want to have
a contest of strength?

388
00:24:46.870 --> 00:24:48.360
Well?!

389
00:25:00.880 --> 00:25:04.050
Shall we continue, Baroque Works?

390
00:25:04.050 --> 00:25:06.650
Fighting isn't a joke.

391
00:25:34.850 --> 00:25:37.700
M-Miss Monday was overpowered...!

392
00:25:37.700 --> 00:25:40.370
I-Impossible! This can't be true...!

393
00:25:40.370 --> 00:25:44.350
I-I got it! The Marines made
a mistake on that wanted poster.

394
00:25:44.350 --> 00:25:50.380
I see. It makes sense if this guy has
a 30-million-belly bounty on his head.

395
00:25:50.380 --> 00:25:53.040
He is the real captain.

396
00:25:53.040 --> 00:25:54.640
Right.

397
00:25:54.640 --> 00:25:58.720
I thought it was strange that such a
namby-pamby guy was worth 30 million belly.

398
00:25:59.990 --> 00:26:02.760
But, even so, how disgraceful...

399
00:26:02.760 --> 00:26:05.630
If we lose against
one pirate swordsman,

400
00:26:05.630 --> 00:26:10.770
we'll be held responsible since
the boss put us in charge of this town.

401
00:26:10.770 --> 00:26:14.670
It seems that it's finally
our turn to fight.

402
00:26:14.670 --> 00:26:19.440
You may know this, but with
members of Baroque Works,

403
00:26:19.440 --> 00:26:23.680
the smaller his number, the higher
his level and destructive power are.

404
00:26:23.680 --> 00:26:29.790
The three of us, Mr. 9,
Mr. 8 and Miss Wednesday

405
00:26:29.790 --> 00:26:32.340
are agents with a single digit number,

406
00:26:32.340 --> 00:26:38.360
which means we're powerful people
and stronger than those you just beat.

407
00:26:38.360 --> 00:26:42.700
Hmph. Aren't titles useless
when it comes to fighting?

408
00:26:42.700 --> 00:26:45.300
The stronger one wins. That's all.

409
00:26:47.260 --> 00:26:48.560
Igarappa!

410
00:26:49.730 --> 00:26:51.560
Let's go, Miss Wednesday!

411
00:26:51.560 --> 00:26:54.030
Okay, Mr. 9!

412
00:26:55.310 --> 00:26:56.970
Come, Karoo!

413
00:27:00.670 --> 00:27:03.110
I didn't say "give me your hand"!
Come over here!

414
00:27:04.320 --> 00:27:08.070
Now, show him your quick speed
that leaves leopards in the dust!

415
00:27:10.320 --> 00:27:12.350
Who said "sit"?!

416
00:27:13.990 --> 00:27:16.490
What the hell is that?

417
00:27:16.490 --> 00:27:18.450
Can you afford to
let your guard down?

418
00:27:18.790 --> 00:27:21.890
Follow my acrobatics, if you can!

419
00:27:21.890 --> 00:27:24.500
Hot-blooded...

420
00:27:24.500 --> 00:27:25.830
Bat of Guts!

421
00:27:28.340 --> 00:27:30.970
These're metallic bats. Be careful
not to chip your blades on them.

422
00:27:34.350 --> 00:27:37.080
What's the matter? Are you
so frightened you can't move?

423
00:27:41.290 --> 00:27:44.230
What happened to
your proud acrobatics?

424
00:27:44.550 --> 00:27:46.420
If you wanna see it that bad,
watch carefully!

425
00:27:46.560 --> 00:27:47.890
Ahh...

426
00:27:54.750 --> 00:27:58.070
Don't they have anyone better?

427
00:27:58.070 --> 00:28:00.580
Anyone better? That would be me!

428
00:28:00.580 --> 00:28:04.250
Be prepared... Mr. Bushido!

429
00:28:04.250 --> 00:28:08.720
Now, take in my allure
to your heart's content!

430
00:28:08.720 --> 00:28:12.120
Charming Perfume Dance!

431
00:28:17.000 --> 00:28:18.790
Good boy...

432
00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:26.260
I'll finish you off with...

433
00:28:26.260 --> 00:28:28.190
Peacock Slasher!

434
00:28:28.610 --> 00:28:29.940
Go, Karoo!

435
00:28:35.260 --> 00:28:36.700
You went too far!

436
00:28:42.960 --> 00:28:46.620
Fighting these guys is
starting to get embarrassing...

437
00:28:53.300 --> 00:28:55.960
He escaped below using that hole.

438
00:28:57.970 --> 00:29:00.130
That's useless...

439
00:29:02.190 --> 00:29:06.380
Get a good taste of how
frightening I really am!

440
00:29:06.380 --> 00:29:08.900
That shotgun of his is a pain...

441
00:29:08.900 --> 00:29:10.870
How should I close the distance?

442
00:29:11.980 --> 00:29:13.820
Ka-boom!

443
00:29:16.370 --> 00:29:19.990
How dare you beat me like that earlier!

444
00:29:19.990 --> 00:29:21.660
You won't get away with it!

445
00:29:21.660 --> 00:29:23.840
You fell on your own!

446
00:29:23.840 --> 00:29:26.420
Home Run Sneaky Bat!

447
00:29:29.940 --> 00:29:32.170
I tied up one of your arms!

448
00:29:32.170 --> 00:29:33.800
It's an iron chain...

449
00:29:34.940 --> 00:29:37.610
You caught him.

450
00:29:37.610 --> 00:29:40.950
Mr. 8, do it now!

451
00:29:40.950 --> 00:29:42.000
I won't let you escape!

452
00:29:42.430 --> 00:29:44.430
That's right. Don't move.

453
00:29:44.930 --> 00:29:49.830
If you make a stupid move, I'll have to
take your precious friend's life as well.

454
00:29:52.870 --> 00:29:59.520
Good job, Miss Wednesday.
You can't escape or attack now.

455
00:29:59.950 --> 00:30:03.550
That idiot! At least wake up
when you're being held hostage!

456
00:30:03.550 --> 00:30:05.380
Prepare to open fire!

457
00:30:07.550 --> 00:30:09.950
Preparations completed!

458
00:30:09.950 --> 00:30:11.540
What?!

459
00:30:12.760 --> 00:30:14.900
Igarappappa!

460
00:30:15.560 --> 00:30:17.150
Is he a toy?!

461
00:30:35.180 --> 00:30:36.990
Igarappappa!

462
00:30:37.290 --> 00:30:38.590
Igarappappa!

463
00:30:39.090 --> 00:30:40.890
Luffy! Let me use your belly!

464
00:30:42.160 --> 00:30:42.790
What?!

465
00:30:53.670 --> 00:30:55.050
Okay! Done!
